46
00:04:34,310 --> 00:04:36,049
in our investigation.

47
00:04:36,050 --> 00:04:37,519
This is a formal declaration

48
00:04:37,520 --> 00:04:39,179
that from now on the enquiry

49
00:04:39,180 --> 00:04:43,480
will be focusing on a particular
individual.

50
00:04:45,260 --> 00:04:49,400
Our prime suspect,
Paul Spector.

51
00:04:50,780 --> 00:04:54,899
<i>Paul Spector was caught
on CCTV at the botanic gardens</i>

52
00:04:54,900 --> 00:04:57,250
<i>on Saturday 14th April,</i>

53
00:04:58,010 --> 00:05:01,050
<i>the day that Sarah Kay
was there with her sister.</i>

54
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:05,059
<i>He came in to the police station</i>
on Saturday 21st

55
00:05:05,060 --> 00:05:08,379
and was interviewed by DCI Brink.

56
00:05:08,380 --> 00:05:10,909
He gave his DNA
and his fingerprints

57
00:05:10,910 --> 00:05:13,980
and was, at that point, eliminated.

58
00:05:15,140 --> 00:05:17,729
We now have tangible evidence

59
00:05:17,730 --> 00:05:22,550
to link Paul Spector
to the murder of Joe Brawley.

60
00:05:23,100 --> 00:05:26,959
Namely his fingerprints
on a pair of decorating shears,

61
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:30,130
identical to a pair purchased
by Annie Brawley.

62
00:05:32,940 --> 00:05:35,819
<i>Do we need to put an arrest
strategy in place?</i>

63
00:05:35,820 --> 00:05:37,329
<i>Not yet.</i>

64
00:05:37,330 --> 00:05:39,539
<i>There's very good reason
for believing that</i>

65
00:05:39,540 --> 00:05:41,969
<i>Paul Spector is also responsible</i>

66
00:05:41,970 --> 00:05:45,710
<i>for the abduction and unlawful
imprisonment of Rose Stagg.</i>

67
00:05:46,220 --> 00:05:50,429
Last night, I received a phone
call on my old private number

68
00:05:50,430 --> 00:05:53,539
from Rose Stagg's
mobile phone.

69
00:05:53,540 --> 00:05:55,419
The call he made on Rose's phone

70
00:05:55,420 --> 00:05:57,649
last night has been triangulated.

71
00:05:57,650 --> 00:06:00,549
We have a location.
A search is under way.

72
00:06:00,550 --> 00:06:03,759
We have a live cell trace on
Spector's registered mobile phone

73
00:06:03,760 --> 00:06:05,939
and we have his historic
phone records.

74
00:06:05,940 --> 00:06:07,499
Right now that phone is off

75
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:09,819
but we know he has access
to other phones.

76
00:06:09,820 --> 00:06:12,920
He made calls in Scotland,
so we know he did go away.

77
00:06:13,460 --> 00:06:15,899
Yesterday, he made
and received a call

78
00:06:15,900 --> 00:06:18,429
in the vicinity of the
city hospital in Belfast,

79
00:06:18,430 --> 00:06:20,239
so we know he's back.

80
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:21,549
Does he have a car?

81
00:06:21,550 --> 00:06:23,209
He reported his car as stolen

82
00:06:23,210 --> 00:06:25,349
the day after the Brawley murder.

83
00:06:25,350 --> 00:06:27,469
It was a Peugeot 405.

84
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:32,169
Registration - sierra, India,
whisky, three, one, six, zero.

85
00:06:32,170 --> 00:06:34,550
- Has he made an insurance claim?
- No.

86
00:06:35,180 --> 00:06:37,100
We need to find that car.

87
00:07:12,610 --> 00:07:17,019
DCI Matt Eastwood
is my new deputy SIO.

88
00:07:17,020 --> 00:07:19,920
Thus far, he's been covering
the Rose Stagg disappearance.

89
00:07:20,710 --> 00:07:23,959
We have some CCTV footage
that you may not have

90
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:25,950
seen of Rose shopping.

91
00:07:27,300 --> 00:07:30,380
This is her last known
appearance in public.

92
00:07:33,500 --> 00:07:35,279
All the evidence
thus far suggests

93
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:37,119
that Rose was
abducted from her home

94
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:38,949
by an individual who,

95
00:07:38,950 --> 00:07:42,569
in conversation with Rose's
daughter, Nancy, aged six,

96
00:07:42,570 --> 00:07:44,359
called himself Peter.

97
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:48,480
Now, on that point, we have
the suspect's birth certificate.

98
00:07:51,590 --> 00:07:53,089
Peter Paul Spector.

99
00:07:53,090 --> 00:07:56,669
Mother, Mary.
Father, John Paul Spector.

100
00:07:56,670 --> 00:07:59,630
Note the occupation.
Private British Army.

101
00:08:00,150 --> 00:08:02,709
He began an 18-month tour of duty
here in March 1978

102
00:08:02,710 --> 00:08:06,369
with the Duke of
Cumbria's Regiment,

103
00:08:06,370 --> 00:08:07,779
Third Battalion.

104
00:08:07,780 --> 00:08:11,359
Now, Spector was born, as you can
see, on the 25th of May 1979.

105
00:08:11,360 --> 00:08:13,039
The year the Shankill Butchers
were sentenced

106
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:15,119
to life imprisonment
for 19 murders,

107
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:17,130
the year of Warrenpoint.

108
00:08:17,850 --> 00:08:19,300
A bad year.

109
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:23,879
Spector is a married man.
Married in 2004.

110
00:08:23,880 --> 00:08:25,489
Sally-Ann Goodall.

111
00:08:25,490 --> 00:08:29,590
He has two children -
Olivia, eight, and Liam, five.

112
00:08:30,470 --> 00:08:32,099
Sally-Ann's a senior staff nurse

113
00:08:32,100 --> 00:08:34,679
in the Belfast neo-natal
intensive care unit.

114
00:08:34,680 --> 00:08:38,109
She leads a team that has
responsibility for 30 beds.

115
00:08:38,110 --> 00:08:39,999
We have Sally-Ann under
surveillance

116
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:42,330
in the hope that she'll lead us
to her husband.

117
00:08:42,910 --> 00:08:45,830
Our priority is to find him.

118
00:08:46,190 --> 00:08:48,399
<i>Find him,
put him under surveillance</i>

119
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:50,470
<i>in the hope that he
will lead us to Rose.</i>

120
00:08:56,710 --> 00:09:00,550
<i>We know next to nothing
about Paul Spector's childhood.</i>

121
00:09:00,950 --> 00:09:04,789
All we have is a list of children's
homes that he himself provided.

122
00:09:04,790 --> 00:09:07,450
All of those need to be checked out.

123
00:09:07,870 --> 00:09:09,809
A man doesn't wake up
one morning

124
00:09:09,810 --> 00:09:12,519
and find that he has become
a sexual psychopath.

125
00:09:12,520 --> 00:09:15,839
Nor does he wake up one day and
discover that the condition has gone.

126
00:09:15,840 --> 00:09:19,350
It develops over a very long
period of time.

127
00:09:20,710 --> 00:09:24,470
<i>We need to find out everything that
we possibly can about Paul Spector.</i>

128
00:09:26,150 --> 00:09:27,929
<i>Every detail of his life</i>

129
00:09:27,930 --> 00:09:31,440
<i>needs to be established,
checked and double-checked.</i>

130
00:09:33,270 --> 00:09:37,289
I also believe that Paul Spector
is responsible for the deaths

131
00:09:37,290 --> 00:09:41,420
of Fiona Gallagher,
Alice Monroe and Sarah Kay.

132
00:09:41,870 --> 00:09:44,229
I'd say all of his
previous victims

133
00:09:44,230 --> 00:09:47,399
were dead within
an hour of being attacked.

134
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:49,399
She's lost to us already?

135
00:09:49,400 --> 00:09:53,519
The one glimmer of hope
is that he knows Rose.

136
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:58,450
Not from watching and stalking,
objectifying her.

137
00:09:59,150 --> 00:10:00,910
He really knows her.

138
00:10:01,470 --> 00:10:03,170
And she's a mother.

139
00:10:03,570 --> 00:10:05,450
<i>I feel sorry for you,</i>

140
00:10:06,490 --> 00:10:07,950
I really do.

141
00:10:10,050 --> 00:10:12,009
<i>You must have had
a terrible childhood</i>

142
00:10:12,010 --> 00:10:14,040
<i>to be able to do this to me.</i>

143
00:10:15,370 --> 00:10:17,770
<i>I feel sorry for you,</i>

144
00:10:18,480 --> 00:10:20,250
<i>I really do.</i>

145
00:10:21,110 --> 00:10:23,250
<i>I feel sorry for you.</i>

146
00:10:27,470 --> 00:10:30,209
Pay a follow-up call
to Sally-Ann Spector.

147
00:10:30,210 --> 00:10:31,899
Make it seem routine.

148
00:10:31,900 --> 00:10:34,159
Ask her to account for the night
that she was at work

149
00:10:34,160 --> 00:10:37,229
and Spector told us that he was
at home alone with the kids.

150
00:10:37,230 --> 00:10:39,089
The night of the Joe
Brawley murder?

151
00:10:39,090 --> 00:10:41,629
Just that night, though.
Don't spook her too much.

152
00:10:41,630 --> 00:10:43,090
So just a little?

153
00:10:43,550 --> 00:10:45,950
- Take McNally.
- Thank you, ma'am.

154
00:10:48,140 --> 00:10:49,699
She wants me for herself,
really.

155
00:10:49,700 --> 00:10:51,270
She's just being generous.

156
00:11:05,550 --> 00:11:08,949
Do you carry that stuff about bombs
and shootings around in your head?

157
00:11:08,950 --> 00:11:10,710
Etched on my soul.

158
00:11:25,690 --> 00:11:27,139
X-Ray One to Control,

159
00:11:27,140 --> 00:11:29,610
that's a CID car pulling
up at the target's address.

160
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:31,669
<i>Control, from X-Ray One.</i>

161
00:11:31,670 --> 00:11:34,150
<i>CID car pulling up
at the target's address.</i>

162
00:11:36,930 --> 00:11:39,690
That's two CID officers
at the target's door.

163
00:11:48,610 --> 00:11:51,470
Female at the door,
possibly the target's wife.

164
00:11:52,250 --> 00:11:54,910
Two CID officers enter the house.

165
00:11:56,050 --> 00:11:57,650
Doors closed.

166
00:12:03,330 --> 00:12:06,009
I don't know if you remember me,
Mrs Spector.

167
00:12:06,010 --> 00:12:07,749
I spoke to you on the phone
a while ago.

168
00:12:07,750 --> 00:12:09,439
Yes, I do remember.

169
00:12:09,440 --> 00:12:12,059
I'm sorry to intrude like this,
but there are a few questions

170
00:12:12,060 --> 00:12:15,339
I should have asked you
about the night of the 20th.

171
00:12:15,340 --> 00:12:17,800
- What questions?
- They're just routine.

172
00:12:18,250 --> 00:12:20,050
I should have asked you at the time.

173
00:12:21,410 --> 00:12:23,190
You were working, you said?

174
00:12:24,630 --> 00:12:26,739
I wasn't meant to be working
that night.

175
00:12:26,740 --> 00:12:28,299
I'd been on all day.

176
00:12:28,300 --> 00:12:30,949
We'd withdrawn care from one
of the babies in the unit

177
00:12:30,950 --> 00:12:33,009
so I stayed with
the mother to see it through.

178
00:12:33,010 --> 00:12:35,119
And Paul was at home
with the children?

179
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:37,129
He told my colleague
that he was at home

180
00:12:37,130 --> 00:12:39,190
all evening and all night
with the children.

181
00:12:42,570 --> 00:12:46,769
Bathed them, put them to bed,
read them a story.

182
00:12:46,770 --> 00:12:50,190
He said that after that he was
in his study listening to music.

183
00:12:53,530 --> 00:12:55,969
I'm not sure.

184
00:12:55,970 --> 00:12:57,929
It's OK, Mrs Spector.

185
00:12:57,930 --> 00:13:00,879
We just want to be able to eliminate
your husband from our enquiries

186
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:02,189
and move on.

187
00:13:02,190 --> 00:13:04,090
Just tell us what you know.

188
00:13:12,570 --> 00:13:14,130
A friend of mine...

189
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:17,380
A friend of mine picked up
the children from school.

190
00:13:18,170 --> 00:13:19,839
She was looking after them
until nine.

191
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:22,190
She couldn't stay any longer.

192
00:13:23,010 --> 00:13:25,139
So when I couldn't
get hold of Paul,

193
00:13:25,140 --> 00:13:27,719
I called our usual baby-sitter.

194
00:13:27,720 --> 00:13:29,650
She came and stayed the night.

195
00:13:30,170 --> 00:13:33,550
She was gone when I got back
the following morning.

196
00:13:34,150 --> 00:13:35,620
Paul was here.

197
00:13:37,010 --> 00:13:40,009
Can I get those names from you,
Sally?

198
00:13:40,010 --> 00:13:42,630
The friend?
The baby-sitter?

199
00:14:45,090 --> 00:14:46,900
- Talk to you, ma'am?
- Yeah.

200
00:14:47,610 --> 00:14:51,269
According to Mrs Spector,
a baby-sitter - Katerina Benedetto,

201
00:14:51,270 --> 00:14:53,659
known as Katie -
was at the Spectors' house

202
00:14:53,660 --> 00:14:55,529
on the night of the
Joe Brawley murder,

203
00:14:55,530 --> 00:14:58,129
Not Spector himself.

204
00:14:58,130 --> 00:15:00,459
- How old?
- 15 at the time,

205
00:15:00,460 --> 00:15:01,939
just turned 16.

206
00:15:01,940 --> 00:15:03,740
School student.

207
00:15:04,770 --> 00:15:06,470
Should we talk to her?

208
00:15:06,810 --> 00:15:09,439
Well, she'll need
one of her parents present.

209
00:15:09,440 --> 00:15:11,939
Father's dead, motorcycle
accident three years ago.

210
00:15:11,940 --> 00:15:13,869
He was an art dealer.

211
00:15:13,870 --> 00:15:17,889
Mother works for an auction house.
Fine art -

212
00:15:17,890 --> 00:15:19,529
paintings and stuff.

213
00:15:19,530 --> 00:15:21,490
I know what fine art is.

214
00:15:22,290 --> 00:15:23,970
Pay her a visit.

215
00:15:49,090 --> 00:15:51,059
- Mrs Benedetto?
- Yes.

216
00:15:51,060 --> 00:15:53,299
DC Martin, DC McNally.

217
00:15:53,300 --> 00:15:55,219
We'd like to talk to
your daughter, Katerina.

218
00:15:55,220 --> 00:15:56,689
Is she home?

219
00:15:56,690 --> 00:15:59,810
- Yes, she is. Come on through.
- Thank you. Thanks.

220
00:16:09,410 --> 00:16:10,710
Katie?

221
00:16:11,020 --> 00:16:12,320
Katie!

222
00:16:13,450 --> 00:16:16,450
These police officers
want to talk to you.

223
00:16:19,010 --> 00:16:21,759
When did you start baby-sitting
for the Spectors, Katie?

224
00:16:21,760 --> 00:16:23,569
When I was 14.

225
00:16:23,570 --> 00:16:26,569
And you were baby-sitting
on the night of the 20th?

226
00:16:26,570 --> 00:16:29,129
- And you stayed all night?
- No.

227
00:16:29,130 --> 00:16:30,430
No?

228
00:16:30,750 --> 00:16:33,569
- I left at about three in the morning.
- Really?

229
00:16:33,570 --> 00:16:35,900
You were asleep
and didn't hear me come in.

230
00:16:36,210 --> 00:16:38,419
Did you leave because
Mr Spector came home?

231
00:16:38,420 --> 00:16:42,209
No. I left because we suddenly
realised the time

232
00:16:42,210 --> 00:16:44,089
and he wanted to go to bed.

233
00:16:44,090 --> 00:16:45,579
We?

234
00:16:45,580 --> 00:16:47,950
Paul came home at about 9:30.

235
00:16:48,370 --> 00:16:50,950
- 9:30?
- Yes. I see.

236
00:16:53,210 --> 00:16:55,510
Then why did you stay?

237
00:16:55,820 --> 00:16:59,569
We got talking,
listening to music in his study.

238
00:16:59,570 --> 00:17:03,619
You were alone with Mr Spector
from 9:30 till 3am?

239
00:17:03,620 --> 00:17:05,529
The children were there.

240
00:17:05,530 --> 00:17:08,019
Have you stayed that
late at the Spectors' before?

241
00:17:08,020 --> 00:17:09,320
No.

242
00:17:10,250 --> 00:17:13,009
Where did Sally-Ann suggest
you should sleep that night?

243
00:17:13,010 --> 00:17:15,349
She said to use their bed.

244
00:17:15,350 --> 00:17:17,059
Did you use their bed?

245
00:17:17,060 --> 00:17:19,270
I told you, Paul came home.

246
00:17:19,850 --> 00:17:21,689
Where had he been?

247
00:17:21,690 --> 00:17:23,859
Doing something related to work,
I think.

248
00:17:23,860 --> 00:17:25,890
